BOOLEAN HttpWapMgr::RegisterWap (  INT &  conn_id,
INT  pr_id,
WString &  mime,
INT  app_id = 0
)  [protected, virtual]
 

Used to register for WAP push messages.

Function may be called again after a call to wapUnregister.

Parameters:
conn_id Identifier of the WAP connection. Will be issued and allows a WapHandler to identify itself in function calls. Value is > 0.
pr_id Id of WapProfile to be used (WapProfile determines if connection is secure/non-secure and connection-oriented/ connectionless).
mime MIME type supported by registering application.
app_id Application id according to Open Mobile Naming Authority (OMNA), defaults to 0.
Returns:
Success of method.

BOOLEAN HttpWapMgr::ResumeHttp (  INT  conn_id  )  [protected, virtual]
 

Used by the application to tell the stack to resume sending messages.

This function enables flow control between the WAP stack and the application (not between HTTP client and HTTP server). The behaviour of the WAP stack depends e.g. on timeouts etc. and is implementation specific.

Parameters:
conn_id Identifier of the HTTP connection, conn_id was returned by httpOpen method.
Returns:
Success of method.
